## The MTA Landscape in 2026

The multi-touch attribution market has exploded. There are now 50+ tools claiming to solve marketing measurement—from enterprise platforms costing $100K+/year to scrappy startups at $100/month.

This guide cuts through the noise. We've categorized the major players, compared their features and pricing, and identified which tools work best for different business types. Full disclosure: mbuzz is one of the tools in this comparison. We'll be upfront about where we excel (server-side tracking, transparent pricing, technical teams) and where competitors are the better choice (Shopify-native, enterprise Salesforce, mobile apps).

### The Market Gap: Validated Attribution Costs Too Much

Most attribution tools cluster in one of two places: affordable but basic (top-left), or sophisticated but expensive (bottom-left). The bottom-right quadrant—enterprise unified measurement—exists but requires $50K+ budgets.

**The gap:** Almost no one offers validated, multi-model attribution at accessible prices. That's where mbuzz sits.

